&lt;p&gt;The Pricing Analyst, reporting to Director of Pricing, is responsible for analyzing, optimizing, and continuously refining the company’s pricing strategy across assigned territories and vendors. This role serves as the analytical engine behind pricing decisions—leveraging advanced analysis, forecasting, and scenario modeling to predict outcomes, guide tradeoffs, and drive sustained improvements in price realization and gross margin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a strategic pricing partner to Sales Operations and Regional Sales Leadership, the Pricing Analyst translates market signals and economic insights into actionable pricing decisions. This role operates as both a &lt;strong&gt;strategic advisor and hands‑on individual contributor&lt;/strong&gt;, driving pricing initiatives end‑to‑end while proactively adjusting course based on performance, market response, and competitive dynamics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own pricing strategy execution with a strong emphasis on continuous optimization, performance measurement, and directional pivots based on real‑world results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a strategic thought partner to the Sales Organization by evaluating pricing tradeoffs between volume, margin, competitiveness, and customer behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify when pricing strategies are underperforming and recommend corrective actions, alternative price structures, or tactical adjustments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain pricing models, elasticity analyses, and scenario simulations to forecast the impact of pricing decisions on demand, revenue, margin, and customer retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform pre‑ and post‑implementation pricing analysis to quantify impact versus expectations and refine future strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build forward‑looking business cases that compare alternative pricing strategies and predict outcomes under different market conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use historical performance, deal‑level data, and customer behavior patterns to anticipate risks and opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor evolving market conditions, competitor pricing moves, customer buying behaviors, and cost drivers to inform proactive pricing adjustments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead competitive pricing and value positioning analyses, translating market insights into differentiated pricing recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze industry and customer trends to identify emerging pricing opportunities, structural risks, and long‑term margin implications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze industry trends, competitor offerings, product economics, and margin drivers, synthesizing findings into clear recommendations for management.\&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales Operations to ensure pricing strategies are executable, scalable, and supported by tools and processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track pricing performance KPIs (price realization, discounting behavior, margin leakage) and recommend interventions where targets are missed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive adoption of pricing changes by clearly articulating the “why,” expected impact, and success metrics to stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Analytics, Statistics, Finance, Business, or a related field (or equivalent professional experience).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to develop predictive pricing models, scenario analyses, and data‑backed recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Forex, Trading and revenue analysis is desired&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with exceptional attention to detail and accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective written, verbal, and presentation skills, with the ability to influence without direct authority.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to learn, listen, and share pricing expertise with stakeho

